RIYADH: Al Moammar Information Systems Co. has closed a deal with Al Rajhi Financial Co. to set up a SR1-billion ($266 million) Shariah-compliant investment fund. The special investment fund will be used to finance digital and technical infrastructure projects as well as medical equipment in Saudi Arabia, a bourse filing revealed. Under the deal, information technology provider MIS will be the marketer, supplier, and operator of the fundâ€™s projects, while Al Rajhi will act as the fund manager. The parties expect to complete the procedures to launch the fund by the second half of 2022.